Sentencas: La0.5Sr0.5Co3-delta (LSCO) thin films were deposited on yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) substrates by pulsed laser deposition (PLD) for application to thin film solid oxide fuel cell electrodes.
Titulo: Structure and conducting properties of La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ films on YSZ

Sentencas: During the deposition, the substrate temperature was varied from 450 to 750 degrees C, and the oxygen pressure in the chamber was varied from 80 to 310 mTorr.
Titulo: Structure and conducting properties of La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ films on YSZ

Sentencas: Films deposited at 650 degrees C and an oxygen background pressure of 150 mTorr were mostly (100) oriented.
Titulo: Structure and conducting properties of La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ films on YSZ

Sentencas: Deposition at higher temperatures or under lower oxygen pressures lead to mostly (110) oriented films.
Titulo: Structure and conducting properties of La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ films on YSZ

Sentencas: Films with low electrical resistivity of 10(-3) Omega.cm were obtained.
Titulo: Structure and conducting properties of La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ films on YSZ
